IAB TCF Specification Data (tcf-purposes.json)
-----------------------------------------------
Copyright (C) IAB Europe
License: Proprietary (publicly available standard)
Source: https://vendor-list.consensu.org/v3/vendor-list.json
Specification: IAB Transparency & Consent Framework v2.2 / GVL Spec v3
Usage: TCF purpose definitions (IDs, names, descriptions),
       special purposes, features, and special features used as
       reference data for consent analysis context.

The tcf-purposes.json file contains purpose and feature definitions
from the IAB TCF specification, extracted from the publicly available
Global Vendor List (GVL) API. It does NOT include vendor-specific data.
This data is part of an open industry standard designed for
programmatic consumption by CMPs, publishers, and vendors.


IAB Global Vendor List - Vendor Data (gvl-vendors.json)
-------------------------------------------------------
Copyright (C) IAB Europe
License: Proprietary (publicly available standard)
Source: https://vendor-list.consensu.org/v3/vendor-list.json
Usage: Maps numeric vendor IDs from the IAB TC String to
       human-readable company names, privacy policy URLs, declared
       TCF purpose IDs, and inferred categories for display in
       consent analysis.

The gvl-vendors.json file contains a snapshot of vendor data from the
IAB TCF Global Vendor List (GVL) v3 API, enriched with categories
inferred from declared TCF purposes and cross-referenced against the
project's partner databases and the Disconnect Tracking Protection
list. This data is part of an open industry standard designed for
programmatic consumption.


Google Additional Consent Mode Providers (google-atp-providers.json)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Copyright (C) Google LLC
License: Publicly available reference data
Source: https://storage.googleapis.com/tcfac/additional-consent-providers.csv
Reference: https://support.google.com/admanager/answer/9681920
Usage: Maps numeric provider IDs from the Google AC String to
       company names and privacy-policy URLs for display in consent
       analysis.

The google-atp-providers.json file contains a snapshot of Google's
Ad Technology Provider list. It is compiled from the publicly
available CSV distributed by Google for integration with the IAB
TCF Additional Consent Mode specification.


Project-Curated Data
--------------------
The following data files were authored for this project and do not
originate from third-party datasets. They are covered by the project's
AGPL-3.0-or-later license:

  - trackers/tracking-scripts.json    (493 URL regex patterns)
  - trackers/benign-scripts.json      (51 benign script patterns)
  - trackers/tracking-storage.json    (localStorage/sessionStorage keys)
  - consent/consent-cookies.json      (consent cookie patterns)
  - consent/consent-platforms.json    (CMP platform signatures)
  - consent/gdpr-reference.json       (GDPR/ePrivacy regulatory reference)
  - partners/*.json                   (8 partner classification databases)
  - publishers/media-groups.json      (UK media group ownership data)

These files were compiled from publicly available information including
vendor documentation, company websites, regulatory text, and the IAB
TCF CMP registry. They do not reproduce substantial portions of any
copyrighted dataset.
